==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: asthenosphere
<hw>asthenosphere</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the lower layer of
the earth's crust, below the lithosphere. It is estimated as from fifty
to several hundred miles thick. It is less rigid than the lithosphere,
but still rigid enough to transmit some transverse seismic waves.</def>
<au>[RHUD]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

